What does this tool do?\par
This tool takes exposed parameters from substance designer files(SBAR) and allows you to create up to two keyframes  by manipulating the exposed Variables and animating them.\par
You can Write  variables to XML files and read from them as well.\par
When you are done creating your animated object you can save the object as a Prefab for future use.\par
\par
Notes:\par
\pard{\pntext\f1\'B7\tab}{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf1\pnindent0{\pntxtb\'B7}}\fi-360\li720\sa200\sl276\slmult1 This tool is meant for simple/optimized materials. if you have a giant  Substance Material that is 2048-2048 or has many exposed parameters near the beginning of the input graph in Substance Designer the tool will lag. There are some materials that I have made and included in this  project that are not meant to be used by this tool(Sand,Rock). I have included them as examples.  \par
{\pntext\f1\'B7\tab}Allegorithmic has a video about optimizing substances for unity: {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=VnhIDRcfAWA"}}{\fldrslt{\ul\cf1 https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=VnhIDRcfAWA}}}\f0\fs22\par
{\pntext\f1\'B7\tab}The Rock material has a boolean(true/false) called Surface Mode in the inspector. you will not be able to see the diffrence in some variables depending on which mode it is set to. \par
{\pntext\f1\'B7\tab}Expect  read XML files to break when using diffrent versions of this tool\par
{\pntext\f1\'B7\tab}Try not to delete objects while in play mode(if you do, exit playmode and restart). \par
{\pntext\f1\'B7\tab}Try not to use the tool on animated prefabs already created with this tool\par
\pard\sa200\sl276\slmult1\par
